                        Smyth
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v10</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d873</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">873</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-05-05T22:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-05-05T22:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-05T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-05T22:00:00-05:00" n="873" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d873">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Chase, Augustus: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-06T11:00:00+08:00">May 6, 1946—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 6—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>752. [To Mukden:] Proposal in your unnumbered April 30, 4 p.m.<note n="26" xml:id="d873fn26">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> that Chase proceed Harbin accompanied
                    by Rigg, communications equipment, and such personnel as you deem immediately
                    essential as soon as transportation available is approved.</p>
                <p>Executive Headquarters [at] Peiping has been informed to offer you assistance.
                    You should consult Robertson<note n="27" xml:id="d873fn27">Walter S. Robertson,
                        American Commissioner at Executive Headquarters at Peiping.</note> [at]
                    Peiping before making approach Communist representatives Mukden.</p>
                <p>Sent to Mukden as 7, May 6, 11 a.m., repeated to Dept. as 752; repeated to
                    Peiping for Robertson as 45.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
